// RULE (NOT yet enforced — EXPECTED TO FAIL until it is):
//   You import a DEVICE by name and a plain MODULE by path. A bare name in `#import { … }` must
//   resolve to a device (a unit with a `.ds.arche` datasheet); a non-device imported by bare name is
//   an error telling you to import it by path instead (`#import { "./plainmod" }`).
//   `plainmod` has no datasheet, so importing it by name must error.
//
// Today `#import { plainmod }` succeeds, so the grep finds no error and the test FAILS.
// RUN: %arche build -o %t %s > %t.out 2>&1 ; grep -qiE "by path|not a device|import .* by path|only devices.*by name" %t.out
#import { plainmod }

main :: proc() {
  _v := plainmod.greet();
}
